fn.p:
The hazard function is expressed as H(dij
) = Pr(D < dij
) and the survival function is S(dij
) = 1 – H(dij
) = Pr(D ≥ dij
). From these identities, it is easy to see that whereas the hazard function, H(dij
), expresses the conditional probability of distance terminating, the survival function, S(dij
), expresses the conditional probability of distance extending.
